<p>So the Fourier transform can be seen as a sort of phase coherent sum of all of the STFTs of <i>x</i>(<i>t</i>).  Since the inverse Fourier transform is
</p>
<dl><dd><span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle x(t)={\frac {1}{2\pi }}\int _{-\infty }^{\infty }X(\omega )e^{+i\omega t}\,d\omega ,}">
