</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/6a28e00f9132204db58dca60c49d0e473398777a" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.505ex; width:42.053ex; height:6.176ex;" alt="{\displaystyle x(t)=\int _{-\infty }^{\infty }\left[{\frac {1}{2\pi }}\int _{-\infty }^{\infty }X(\tau ,\omega )e^{+i\omega t}\,d\omega \right]\,d\tau .}"></span></dd></dl>
<p>It can be seen, comparing to above that windowed "grain" or "wavelet" of <i>x</i>(<i>t</i>) is
</p>
<dl><dd><span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle x(t)w(t-\tau )={\frac {1}{2\pi }}\int _{-\infty }^{\infty }X(\tau ,\omega )e^{+i\omega t}\,d\omega .}">
