  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/f3c0eae04cf10d69d1e025b0727e5d4339c281a1" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.505ex; width:36.777ex; height:6.009ex;" alt="{\displaystyle X(t,f)=\int _{-\infty }^{\infty }w(t-\tau )x(\tau )e^{-j2\pi f\tau }d\tau }"></span></dd></dl>
<p>We can have a simple example:
</p><p>w(t) = 1     for |t| smaller than or equal B
</p><p>w(t) = 0     otherwise
</p><p>B = window
</p><p>Now the original function of the Short-time Fourier transform can be changed as
</p>
<dl><dd><span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle X(t,f)=\int _{t-B}^{t+B}x(\tau )e^{-j2\pi f\tau }d\tau }">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mi>X</mi>
        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
        <mi>t</mi>
        <mo>,</mo>
        <mi>f</mi>
        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
        <mo>=</mo>
        <msubsup>
          <mo>&#x222B;<!-- ∫ --></mo>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>t</mi>
            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- − --></mo>
            <mi>B</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>t</mi>
            <mo>+</mo>
            <mi>B</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msubsup>
